<HEADLINE> Rwandan President Hails 1997 Achievements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 1 (Xinhua) --Rwandan President Pasteur
Bizimungu said, in his adress to the nation on New Year's Eve,
that Rwanda is emerging from the darkness to light, Rwanda News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Among the biggest achievements the Rwandan government scored
in 1997, he cited the successful repatriation and resettlement of
over one million Rwandan nationals from neighboring countries,
the consolidation of the policy of national reconciliation and
the stabilization of the national economy that has noted a steady
growth in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
He said his government will put an utmost focus on supporting
incoming generating activities aimed at stimulating economic
growth, and eradication of poverty and ignorance.
</P>
<P>
The president, however, also regretted that problems of
insecurity, most specially in the north-west, continue to be a
serious setback to the country.
</P>
<P>
He condemned acts of killings by Hutu extremists who committed
genocide in 1994 and have not given up their heinous agenda.
</P>
<P>
He strongly warned the population of the insecurity-affected
Gisenyi and Ruhengeri prefectures backing the armed rebellion
that they will face the harsh repercussions of the fires
they are fanning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
