<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 100 Civilians, 30 Rebels Killed in Burundi Strife </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 1 (Xinhua) --Hutu rebels in Burundi on
Wednesday night massacred over 100 civilians near the capital of
Bujumbura in retaliation for the killing of their 30 companions
by the Burundi army, Rwanda News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the Burundi army spokesman Mames Sinarinzi
as saying that a very important group of armed Hutu rebels
attempted to storm a military barracks near the capital's airport
on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
They were repulsed by the army that killed 30 of the
assailants, who then crossed the airport causing some minor
damages to the airport's vehicles and buildings, he added.
</P>
<P>
But in retreating, the rebels raided the Rukarama Village,
near the capital massacring over 100 civilians, most of whom
women and children who could not run away from the attack,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
"The casualty figure might rise as we are still finding more
bodies," Mames declared.
</P>
<P>
The government lost two soldiers, three others were wounded in
the attack, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
