<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Bombing, Traffic Accidents in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- A grenade bombing and several
traffic accidents, in which two people were killed and
some others injured, marked the beginning of the new year in
Luanda, capital of Angola.
</P>
<P>
According to state radio today, the bombing occurred at the
center of the capital on New Year's Eve, killing one person on
the spot and injured three others, said a source of the National
Police Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The offender is a soldier from the armed forces of
Angola who has been arrested by the police.
</P>
<P>
On the jovial occasion, three traffic accidents were also
recorded in Luanda with one person killed and several others
wounded, the radio said.  
</P>
