<HEADLINE> Thousands of Palestinians Celebrate Fatah's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Palestinians took
to the streets today in Gaza and the West Bank city of Ramallah
to celebrate the 33rd anniversary of the founding of Fatah, the
main faction of the Palestine Liberation Organization.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators from all walks of life in the Palestinian
territories, shouted anti-Israeli slogans and burned Israeli flags
during the celebrations.
</P>
<P>
Some demonstrators, dressed in army uniforms, even shot
automatic rifles and short-guns into the air, demanding Israel to
leave the occupied Palestinian territories as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators also pledged to support President of the
Palestinian National Authority Yasser Arafat to move the Middle
East peace process forward under the signed Oslo Accords.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the Israeli security forces today
destroyed two tunnels in Gaza Strip's Rafiah area bordering
Egypt, according to Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli security forces said the two tunnels had been
used by the Palestinians to smuggle weapons from Egypt.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, three similar tunnels were destroyed by the Israeli
security forces in the same area for the same reason.
</P>
