back to prison if he does not abide by the conditions and police
orders.
</P>
<P>
Kaunda was arrested last Thursday allegedly in connection with
the October 28 abortive coup. He returned home last Monday after
a Marathon overseas trip, which took him to India, South Africa,
Zimbabwe, the United States and Britain among other countries.
</P>
<P>
He went abroad on the eve of the coup to seek international
pressure on the government.
</P>
<P>
After Kaunda's arrest his United National Independence Party
(UNIP) pulled out of dialogue with the government.
</P>
<P>
Deputy secretary for publicity and information of UNIP P.S.
Chitambla said here today that the party will soon make its stand
known on Kaunda's release and house arrest. 
