<HEADLINE> East China Province to Merge Foreign Trade Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, January 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi
Province is preparing to merge the province's eight biggest
foreign trade companies into a single group to increase its
competitiveness in world trade.
</P>
<P>
The province exported 1.42 billion U.S. dollars of goods by
December, 1997, 14.38 percent more than the same period in 1996,
but the growth rate is lower than that for the coastal regions,
said Chen Barong, deputy secretary general of the provincial
government.
</P>
<P>
The processing trade is only 16 percent of the provincial
total, while the rations of machinery and electronics in the
provincial total decreased to seven percent from 10 percent during
the 1991-1995 period, the official said.  
