<HEADLINE> HK Eligible Voters Urged to Get Registered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Woo Kwok-hing, chairman of the
Electoral Affairs Commission of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), Friday urged local eligible people,
who have not signed up yet as electors for the upcoming
legislative elections, to get registered as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference on the voter registration, Woo
said: "With two more weeks to go before the registration deadline
closes on January 16, more than a million eligible people have yet
to sign up as electors for the first Legislative Council election
of the SAR."
</P>
<P>
He urged eligible permanent residents not to forgo their
rights, warning: "If you do not register before January 16, you
will not be able to choose a legislative council member to
represent you."
</P>
<P>
Among 6.3 million Hong Kong citizens, a total of over 2.5
million people are eligible to take part in the elections
scheduled for May.
</P>
<P>
In early December, a total of 30,000 voter registration
ambassadors knocked on every door all over the SAR to help
residents sign up as electors for the elections.
</P>
<P>
These voter registration ambassadors, who are teen-age
students, have visited nearly two million households during the
voter registration week from December 6 to 12.
</P>
<P>
"The door-to-door visits have been an excellent lesson on civic
education for the young students," Woo told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He also said that although the door-to-door visits have been
successfully concluded, the Home Affairs Department of the SAR
government has no let-up in their efforts to register as many
people as possible.
</P>
<P>
A targeted approach is now under way with visits to young
people at tertiary institutes and youth centers, while large
public organizations and charitable bodies are actively involved
in getting their employees to register.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Home Affairs Department has also set up counters
at MTR stations and bus termini to help people sign up.  
</P>
