<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Dip, Volume Falls to New Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices fell
slightly in sluggish transactions on the first trading day in the
new year.
</P>
<P>
Turnover slumped to 2.821 billion HK dollars (362 million US
dollars), breaking the single-day record low of 3.254 billion HK
dollars (417 million US dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
The volume of transactions surpassed 46 billion HK dollars (5.9
billion US dollars) on August 29, 1997, the highest one-day
turnover in the history of the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong (SEHK).
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index closed at 10,680.57, shedding 42.19 points
or 0.39 percent from the previous trading session on the New
Year's Eve. Property shares edged up, while banking, utilities,
commercial and industrial counters all went down.
</P>
<P>
H shares, namely China state-owned enterprises listed on the
Hong Kong bourse, also dropped, but red chips remained almost
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The 33-member blue chip index opened higher Friday morning at
10,743.68 points and reached the day's high of 10,822.67 in the
first hour of trading, but lost ground later.  
</P>
</TEXT>
