<P>
More than 20 university students in Shijiazhuang City went to
the railway station to help passengers with their luggage. The
practice had been handed down by different classes of students for
a dozen years.
</P>
<P>
This morning, nearly 10,000 young people went to the streets,
transportion terminals, urban squares and scenic areas to offer
free services.
</P>
<P>
Young volunteers in a number of cities in northeast China's
Heilongjiang Province were mobilized to pick up road garbage,
scrub street lamps, repair roadside chairs, maintain traffic
order, and enjoy the holiday with the elderly.
</P>
<P>
Residents of Changchun City woke up this morning to find the
city coated with heavy snow. Early in the morning, young
volunteers in red caps went to the city's railway station to help
passengers carry their luggage or inform them of the use of
medicines in travel. Some youths sent rice, flour or edible oil to
poor homes.
</P>
<P>
Young workers in the Tianjin City Railway Bureau gave up their
holiday rest to carry out overall checking of railway equipment.
</P>
<P>
In Shanghai, university students accompanied the handicapped
elderly to visit the Shanghai Museum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
