<HEADLINE> Singapore-Malaysia Second Link Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The 1.9-km Second Link from
Tuas, western Singapore, to Gelang Patah in Johor, Malaysia,
opened to traffic on Friday, after almost four years of
construction work by the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The project is a fast new way for Singaporeans to reach the
North-South Highway in Malaysia and will help ease the jam on the
Causeway, the first link between Woodlands, Singapore, and Johor
Baru, Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Singapore television report described the Second Link as
"another milestone in Malaysia-Singapore relations" and said that
it will be a toll-free ride for motorists on the new link for one
month from Friday.
</P>
<P>
The television quoted a senior Malaysian government official as
saying that the toll-free passage will stay on until the official
announcement of the rates to be charged.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Ministry of Communications announced recently that it
would not be levying tolls for the first few weeks, and it will be
matching the Malaysian toll rates once they are finalized.
</P>
