the selection of its vice presidential candidate because of the
entry of "outsiders" into the derby.
</P>
<P>
"This is a matter really for the President and the House
Speaker to balance everything, including geographical distribution
of candidates, sectoral distribution of candidates, and also the
vice president should be able to get votes for the president, and
the president should be able to make his vice president win in the
next elections," Torres said.
</P>
<P>
Lakas has its own three vice presidentiables. They are Interior
and Local Government Secretary Robert Barbers, Justice Secretary
Teofisto Guingona and Senator Leticia Ramos-Shahani.
</P>
<P>
Torres said the vice presidential candidate slot is "still open
until probably next week," making it clear that members of the
ruling party will accept the decision of the President as to who
will finally be chosen as the partner of de Venecia.  
