<HEADLINE> Scientists Develop Chinese-Language Computer Keyboard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Scientists have developed the
first computer keyboard for the convenient input of Chinese
characters.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen-based Huarentong Computer Development
Corp. announced that it took 10 years to develop the
Chinese-language keyboard.
</P>
<P>
A scientist working with the company said anyone able to write
Chinese characters can easily input the characters according to
the strokes and writing orders of the Chinese characters.
</P>
<P>
The patented keyboard preserves the original distribution of
keys and functions of the English-language keyboards. The keyboard
has five areas for the five major types of strokes of Chinese
characters.
</P>
<P>
The screens can display a Chinese character by inputting the
strokes of a character's writing order of its first and second
strokes.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than several hundred methods have been applied in
inputting Chinese characters with English-language keyboards.
</P>
</TEXT>
