<HEADLINE> Crime Rate Drops in Hainan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Haikou, January 2 (Xinhua) -- In 1997 the crime rate in China's
island province of Hainan dropped to the lowest point since 1988.
</P>
<P>
According to provincial public security authorities, the ratio
was eight crimes per ten thousand people, lower than the country's
average.
</P>
<P>
The situation was achieved largely due to the establishment of
a police emergency call network that has covered every corner of
the province.
</P>
<P>
Launched in 1996, the security emergency hot line has helped
police crack down on crimes and handle traffic accidents.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the province's crime rate for last year was
down by 17.7 percent, and serious crimes dropped by 22 percent,
compared with 1996.  
