<HEADLINE> Rwandan Army Kills Ex-Officer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Rwandan army killed a
former government officer, Major Modeste Rwabukwisi, in
southwestern Cyangugu Province, the Rwanda News Agency today
quoted a military source as reporting.
</P>
<P>
"The incident took place Thrusday in Gafunzo commune on the
shores of Lake Kivu," the Brigade Commander of Cyangugu, John
Ruzindaza said.
</P>
<P>
Rwabukwisi underwent military training in Belgium before
returning to the country in the wake of the 1994 genocide. He,
however, had preferred to join the ranks of Hutu militia that
were preparing to invade Rwanda from the former Zaire.
</P>
<P>
Military sources in Cyangugu disclosed that Rwabukwisi was
part of an important group of militiamen that attempted to invade
Cyangugu Town from the Democratic Republic of Congo early last
month.
</P>
<P>
"Some were either killed or tracked down by the local
residents in collaboration with secuirty forces," John Ruzindaza
said.
</P>
<P>
Rwabukwisi was shot dead by security forces as he tried to
flee to the Democratic Republic of Congo through Lake Kivu. A
dozen militiamen believed to be his body-guards were either
captured or killed. 
</P>
