<HEADLINE> French Mirage Fighters to Join Exercise in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Six mirage 2000 D modern combat
aircraft of the French air force will join an international
military exercise to be held from January 12 to February 6 in the
United States, Agence France-Presse (AFP) Friday quoted military
sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
These combat aircraft, which are based in Meurthe-et-Moselle in
eastern France, will leave for the Nellis air force base in Nevada
on Saturday for the "Red Flag" exercise to draw all modern combat
aircraft from around the world.
</P>
<P>
A French air force officer described the "Red Flag" as the
"most realistic" air exercise in the world, as its programs
include testing materials, quality of equipments and combat
tactics in "an entirely reconstituted combat environment."
</P>
<P>
The Mirage 2000 D will test its capability of shooting ground
targets in the daytime as well as in the night-time.
</P>
<P>
The F-15 and F-16 fighters of the U.S. Air Force, the Tornado
fighters of the British Royal Air Force, and the F-16 fighters of
the Singapore air force will also join the exercise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
