<HEADLINE> U.N. Supports Uganda in Fighting Against Cholera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations provides
with 200 million Ugandan Shillings (some 200,000 U.S. Dollars) to
Uganda to fight cholera, The New Vision said today.
</P>
<P>
Thelma Awori, the UN Development Program's regional boss in
Africa, announced about 50 million shillings (some 500,000 U.S.
Dollars) will be used to check the epidemic.
</P>
<P>
Cholera, an epidemic aggravated by poverty, should be checked
urgently, the UNDP boss said.
</P>
<P>
Her organization will review the emergency request from
Ugandan Health Ministry on the matter.
</P>
<P>
She visited treatment centers in Banda and Mulago in Kampala
city, accompanied by Health Minister Crispus Kiyonga.
</P>
<P>
Crispus Kiyonga, Ugandan Health Minister, appealed for help in
fighting against cholera on December 30, saying that his
country's problem in preventing cholera spread is lack of enough
fund and classified specialists. The treatment of a cholera
patient costs 40,000 to 50,000 shillings (some 40-50 U.S.
Dollars) per day, he estimated.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 300 Ugandans have died since the outbreak of the
epidemic three weeks ago. The epidemic situation in the country
is still worsening.
</P>
<P>
"The organism that spreads cholera, Cholera Vibrio, dies
faster under the sun," said Charles Mugero, a specialist in
cholera task force.  
</P>
</TEXT>
