<HEADLINE> Saudi Airliner Makes Emergency Landing in Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 2 (Xinhua) -- A Saudi airliner made an emergency
landing at Cairo airport Friday because of a fire in its luggage
bin, according to local airport officials.
</P>
<P>
With about 350 passengers on board, the Saudia Boeing 747 was
flying over Cairo from Jiddah, Saudi Arabia to London when the fire
was found.
</P>
<P>
