<HEADLINE> Vietnam Produces 11 Million Tons of Coal in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's coal industry mined
nearly 11 million tons of coal last year, a record output that was
13 percent over that of last year, local press reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
By selling nearly 7 million ton of coal at home and another
3.56 million ton abroad, the industry contributed roughly 13
million U.S. dollars to the state budget, up by 15 percent from
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Based on consumption forecasts for 1998, the Vietnam coal
corporation has asked its subsidiaries to excavate 86 kilometers
of tunnels leading to coal mines to expand production.
</P>
<P>
The corporation has also mapped out measures to expand its
foothold in domestic market and a plan to intensify environmental
protection and safety measures in mining activities. 
</P>
