<HEADLINE> Finland Dedicated to Stability in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Finnish President Martti
Ahtisaari and Prime Minister Paavo Lipponen said in their New
Year's messages Thursday that Finland would continue to make
efforts for the stability and development in Europe.
</P>
<P>
In his New Year's message, President Ahtisaari said his country
has got more opportunities of international cooperation in various
fields since the past 10 years.
</P>
<P>
In the military field, Northern Europe is moving towards
cooperation and arms reduction. Ahtisaari said there was good news
that Russian President Boris Yeltsin had announced cutting down
Russia's armed forces in the regions near Northern Europe.
</P>
<P>
Last March Finland became the host country of the U.S.-Russian
summit. The Helsinki summit decided to continue dismarment, deepen
cooperation and give rights to all the countries to solve their
own security and political issues, the Finnish president said.
</P>
<P>
Finland and Russia have developed a more natural
relationship. The Finnish government's initiative for the EU's
development towards Northern Europe has gained unreserved supports
of all parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
He said Finland will contribute to promoting the development of
the relations between the EU and Russia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prime Minister Lipponen said in his New Year's
message Thursday that the decision on the EU's expansion has
provided a historic opportunity to heal the wound that split
Europe in the Cold War period.
</P>
<P>
Finland will support the EU's expansion towards Central and
Eastern Europe and the Baltic countries. It will strive for
joining the European Economic and Monetary Union in the first
group, the prime minister stressed. 
</P>
