<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Unemployment Rate Drops to 10 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's unemployment rate
dropped to 10 percent in 1997 from 13.7 percent in 1995, officials
in the Industrial Development Ministry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The drop was mainly due to the implementation of more than 600
large scale projects and 2,446 small and medium-sized projects
during the period, which provided employment opportunities to
933,000 people, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 1,241 factories expanded their production capacity
during the three years, taking in more employees.
</P>
<P>
These officials said that capital investments on machines and
equipment increased by 35 percent during 1996 and 1997, which
helped improve the country's industrial performance.
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector contributed 35 percent to the country's
economic growth last year, which was around 6 percent.  
</P>
