<DOCNO> XIE19980102.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Province Taking Advantage of Local Strengths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi Province in northwest
China is striving to take full advantage of its rich natural
resources and tourism as well as its strong scientific research
capabilities to fuel an economic boom.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the province should seek more funds,
technologies and markets to make economic gains.
</P>
<P>
Local statistics show that in the last two years the province
has approved about 600 overseas-funded projects and used 1.5
billion U.S. dollars of overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months of 1997, the province's average annual
growth rate of gross domestic product (GDP) reached 10.9 percent,
1.4 percent higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi has abundant natural resources. Ninety-two types of
minerals have been discovered, with deposits of 28 minerals
ranking first to third among all provinces.
</P>
<P>
The province also owns a world-grade, large fine-coal field and
gas production center.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, 13 dynasties established their capital cities in
the province. A long history has brought rich tourism potential
for the province.
</P>
<P>
The province's scientific research capability ranks third in
the country, involving nearly 2,000 research institutions.
</P>
<P>
In spite of rich resources, the economic gap is still widening
between Shaanxi and the coastal areas of the country. And the
province's economic status in the country has dropped relative to
others, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
The exports only accounted for 12 percent of the province's GDP
during 1978-1995 period. And the overseas investment used by
Shaanxi amounted to 4.5 percent of its total fixed assets. The two
indexes are both in the lower half of the national average and
only equal to one-fourth that of some coastal provinces.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi is expected to become a leading province in the field
of economy, industry and tourism by making full use of abundant
mineral resources, technologies and splendid culture, according to
the economic strategy formulated by the local government.
</P>
<P>
To establish economic and technological cooperation with the
outside world, the province took part in all kinds of trade fairs
in Hong Kong, Italy and Japan in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The province invested 240 million yuan to build a 20-kilometer
Xi'an-Lingtong expressway and six years later transferred its
right of use to Hong Kong for 20 years, at a price of 300 million
yuan. The province has thus recovered funds to invest in other
projects.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province transferred 51 percent of shares of
the largest thermal power plant in the northwest, with an
installed capacity of 1.3 million kilowatts, to a Hong Kong
company, collecting 2.75 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
These measures have not only brought funds and advanced
expertise, but also helped the province realize the importance of
a market economy, experts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
