<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga has appointed a one-man commission to probe the recent
riot in the Kalutara Prison where three prisoners died and several
others were injured, the Presidential Secretariat said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The commissioner, High Court Judge A. Rajah Nihal Fernando, has
been empowered to investigate the manner of the prison
administration, the conduct of prison officers and the
circumstances which led to the riot on December 12, 1997.
</P>
<P>
He has also been asked to find out those directly or indirectly
 responsible for the incident and those responsible for causing
injuries and deaths to inmates in the prison,43 kilometers south
of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the commissioner will make recommendations
necessary to prevent the recurrence of such incidents, the
secretariat said.
</P>
<P>
Two Tamils and one Muslim were killed and 17 others injured
when a major clash between the Tamil and Sinhala inmates erupted
in the prison last month.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, Tamil inmates staged a four-day fast in
protest and asked to be transferred to other prisons.  
</P>
