<HEADLINE> Thailand to Suppress Drugs Among Youths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Narcotics Suppression
Bureau proposes a major operational plans revamp in a bid to
distract youths and students from drug sources.
</P>
<P>
Bureau Commissioner pol. lt.-gen. Noppadol Somboonsap was
quoted Friday by local press as saying that the proposal is
supported by Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai who wishes to see
serious action to suppress drugs among youths and in schools.
