<HEADLINE> Two Climbers Survive 600-meter Fall on Mt. Aspring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Two mountain climbers
miraculously survived a 600-meter fall near the summit of Mount
Aspiring, according to media reports on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mark Ryan, 26, and Keith Morrison, 33, both from Wellington,
were recovering a hospital in Dunedin, New Zealand. Ryan has two
broken legs and Morrison suffered back injuries.
</P>
<P>
The pair plummeted down the snow-covered, southwest face of the
3,000-meter mountain on New Zealand's South Island when they were
within half an hour's climb of the summit on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers said Ryan was unconscious after the fall but Morrison
had walked toward a hut to raise the alarm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
