<HEADLINE> Maradona, Napoli Go "Positively" in Negotiation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The talk between Diego
Maradona and Italian Serie A club Napoli about the Argentine star
to be Napoli's president and coach have been "positive", according
to a Buenos Aires TV channel here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Manager Guillermo Coppola just returned from Italy after
negotiating on behalf of Maradona and said the club has proposed a
deal to bring the 1986 World Cup hero back to the club where he
used to play from 1984 to 1991.
</P>
<P>
Napoli, which won its only two Serie A titles with Maradona as
the captain in 1987 and 1990 but later sued him, has fallen to
last place in the Italian first division having lost eight of its
last nine.
</P>
<P>
"This problem is going to be settled in the first days of
January. It all depends on whether Napoli's president Corrado
Ferlaino is willing to give away his club shares," Coppola said.
</P>
<P>
Coppola did not elaborate on Maradona's proposal to the Italian
club.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week Maradona had said that his appointment as
president and coach of Napoli "is almost 60 percent a fact".
</P>
</TEXT>
