<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Tertiary Industry Up in January-October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- China spent 589.2 billion yuan
in the tertiary industry during the first ten months of 1997, up
12.8 percent from the same period of 1996, according to the latest
statistics from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The country's input in transportation, postal and
telecommunications services was 195 billion yuan, up 15.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
That in real estate management, public, residential and
consultancy services stood at 247.7 billion yuan, up 6.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
That in the banking and insurance sectors was 8.1 billion yuan,
up 10.1 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
