<HEADLINE> German to Meet India in Field Hockey Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The German national field
hockey team will play four test matches in India next week, the
Indian Hockey Federation (IHF) said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An IHF spokesman said the series would be staged in Madras,
Bangalore, Amritsar and New Delhi during the period from January
5-11.
</P>
<P>
This is part of the two countries warm-up plans before the
World Cup to be staged in Utrecht, the Netherlands, later this
year. 
