<HEADLINE> Slovakia Beats Germany in Relegation Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia beat Germany 9-0 in
the first of two relegation games on Thursday at the World Junior
Ice Hockey Championship.
</P>
<P>
Ladislav Nagy scored three goals and one assist to inspire the
Slovakians, who were virtually guaranteed to keep their place in
the Pool A.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia needs only a draw in the second game to stay among the
10-team Pool A.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Finland plays Switzerland, and Russia meets the
Czech Republic in the semifinals. 
</P>
