<HEADLINE> China's Retail Sales Up in January-October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- China's retail sales reached
2,151 billion yuan during the first ten months of 1997, up 11.4
percent from the same period of 1996, according to the latest
statistics from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
During the January-October period, the top three consumers were
Guangdong, Jiangsu and Shandong provinces, whose retail sales
stood at 235.6 billion yuan, 171 billion yuan and 153.7 billion
yuan, respectively. 
</P>
