<HEADLINE> Italian Drug Smuggler Seized in Austria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Austrian police have arrested an
Italian drug smuggler carrying 12 kilograms of cocaine encased in
resin.
</P>
<P>
The smuggler, who was taking the cocaine to Rome, was arrested
at the Vienna international airport.
</P>
<P>
Reports said suspicion was aroused among German police by the
smugglers itinerary which showed he was flying from Bogata, in
Colombia, to Vienna via Frankfurt. They alerted Austrian police at
the Vienna Airport.
</P>
<P>
Police at the airport, in 1997, seized 60 kilograms of cocaine
and 25 kilograms of heroin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
