<HEADLINE> Paris-Dakar Auto Rally Starts in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The Paris-Dakar auto rally started
on the New Year's Day here on Thursday with a huge crowd of
spectators watched on.
</P>
<P>
Some 10,000 people turned out to see the competitors off from
Versailles outside Paris while about 65,000 watched the single
12-km timed special section at La Chatre.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Bruno Saby won the stage in nine minutes 45 seconds,
16 seconds ahead of second-placed Kenjiro Shinozuka of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Another Frenchman Jean-Pierre Fontenay was third 13 seconds
further behind.
</P>
<P>
In the motorbike event, defending champion Stephane Peterhansel
from France, managed only a low 15th, 45 seconds behind leading
fellow countryman Francois Flick.
</P>
<P>
Twelve seconds behind Flick was third-placer Andrea Mayer of
Germany.
</P>
<P>
The second stage includes a 35-km timed section outside
Narbonne before the racers head for Granada in Spain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
