<HEADLINE> Granma Asks Cubans To Defend Socialism With Voting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The official daily "Granma"
exhorted Thursday Cuban electors to take part in the legislative
elections of January 11 as an act to defend the almost for decades
of Socialism in the island.
</P>
<P>
The call is contained in an editorial published by Granma and
follows one from Cuban President Fidel Castro issued four days ago
in which he asked Cubans to show the highest involvement in the
incoming suffrages.
</P>
<P>
According to Granma, the organ of the Cuban Communist Party, to
go to the polls "is to protect what we have defended for almost
forty years of revolution, the dignity, the sovereignty, and the
freedom."
</P>
<P>
The editorial, titled "Cuba Calls On Us Again," says that "the
vote for all of our candidates is an act of conscience, justice
and a show of national cohesion, is the tacit reaffirmation of the
decision to which Cubans dedicate ourselves." 
</P>
</TEXT>
