<HEADLINE> Report Warns of Job Losses in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Brazil might lose 2.5 million
jobs in 1998 because of the slowing of economic growth, a report
warned Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report from the Center of Labor Union Studies and Labor
Economy of Brazil says a serious situation will occur if the
government does not take effective measures against the problem.
</P>
<P>
The report said only 2.6 million new jobs have been created in
the country since 1985. Last year, 1.6 million people lost their
jobs, when the economy grew 2.9 percent. If the gross domestic
product grows 1.4 to 2 percent in 1998, more jobs will be lost.
</P>
<P>
The average unemployment rate in Brazil in November was 5.35
percent, the highest figure in any November since 1992.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics estimated
that the unemployment rate will rise to seven or eight percent
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
