<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Detentions of Minors Increase in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Detentions of minors who violate
the law in Ecuador increased almost 30 percent in 1997 compared to
the previous year, said the "Virgilio Guerrero" Center for Youth
Guidance.
</P>
<P>
The figure went from 1,045 minors who entered the center in
1996, to 1,285 in 1997, according to the source.
</P>
<P>
The involvement of boys and girls in crime is a common
phenomenon which is not prevented or controlled in the country,
added the source.
</P>
<P>
Most of the minors detained from January to June were charged
with robbery in 440 cases, followed by holdup, 124: attempt to rob
79, possession of drugs 55, and assault with robbery 53.
</P>
<P>
Minors arrested for driving a vehicle under the influence and
without driver license increased 1,283 percent, and in many cases
they caused an accident.
</P>
<P>
Violations against minors increased 162.5 percent in 1996,
compared with 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to the experts, boys and girls commit violations
because of social phenomena, including maltreatment in the
family. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
