<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Develops High-Speed Laser-Shaping Mill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have developed
high-speed laser-shaping mills which can process resin products of
different sizes, raging from rings to cases of large-size TV sets.
</P>
<P>
The development of high-speed laser-shaping mills is listed
among China's major scientific research projects in its ninth
five-year plan period from 1996 to 2000.
</P>
<P>
The project, launched by Xi'an Jiaotong University, has passed
the provincial level appraisal of experts.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said the high-speed laser-shaping technology was
first developed in Western countries in the early 1990s.
</P>
<P>
They said the computer-controlled laser-shaping mills are
superior to the traditional processing techniques with lathes,
mills, planers and grinders and can make products that need
complicated processing techniques. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
