<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Primary Industry Up 60.9 Percent in January-October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- China spent 26.9 billion yuan in
primary industry, which includes farming, forestry, animal
husbandry, fishery and water conservancy, in the first ten months
of 1997, up 60.9 percent from the same 1996 period, according to
the latest statistics from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the investment in industry and construction sectors
hit 445.1 billion yuan, up 8.4 percent. 
</P>
