<HEADLINE> 17 Die in New Year Revelry in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 17 people were killed
and more than 500 injured as the Philippines welcomed the new year
with firecracker explosion, gun shooting and violence, local
newspaper Manila Bulletin reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted an official report as saying that five of
the fatalities were hit by stray bullets, three died of
firecracker burns while nine others were killed in stabbing and
shooting incidents.
</P>
<P>
Many of those injured needed to have their hands or fingers
amputated while some suffered eye injuries, the report said,
adding that six persons, including two policemen, were arrested
for firing their guns during the New Year revelry.
</P>
<P>
Health Secretary Carmencita Reodica said the injured were being
treated in various hospitals nationwide.
</P>
<P>
She added that the number of victims declined compared with
that of last year thanks to the Health Department's drives
launched against firecracker use and indiscriminate gun shooting.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen people died and 640 were wounded in New Year's revelry
last year while 33 killed and 834 were injured during 1995's New
Year celebrations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980102.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Korean Per Capita Income Down to 9,400 U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, January 2 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's per capita income
dropped to 9,400 U.S. dollars in 1997 from the previous year's
10,548 dollars, said the Ministry of Economy and Finance Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The drop was the first of its kind since 1980 when each South
Korean suffered a slide of 50 dollars due to an oil shock around
the globe.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed the decrease to the failure of the
government's economic policies and the 40 percent devaluation of
South Korean won against the dollar.
</P>
<P>
They said the nation's per capita income will further fall this
year in the aftermath of serious financial crisis caused by the
failure of conglomerates and bad loans of financial institutions
last November.
</P>
<P>
The country's economy, the analysts added, could grind to halt
without speedy assistance from international financial
organizations and industrialized countries.
</P>
<P>
However, South Korea has so far received only 9 billion of the
agreed rescue loans totaling 57 billion dollars from the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) while its won continues to
depreciate.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed with the IMF last December, South
Korea has to completely open its financial market, shut down
ailing commercial banks, and cut its budget while it has to face
massive layoffs.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, South Korea, whose foreign exchange reserve
reportedly stands at about 9 billion dollars, has to pay back
about 25 billion dollars in foreign debts before next February.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980102.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Michael Kennedy Dies in Skiing Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Michael Kennedy, son of the
late Sen. Robert F. Kennedy, was killed Wednesday night in a
skiing accident at Aspen Mountain in Colorado.
</P>
<P>
The 39-year-old Kennedy was skiing with several members of his
family on a slope at the Aspen Mountain resort about 4:15 p.m.
when he crashed into a tree.
</P>
<P>
Ski patrol got to the scene soon and provided first aid as he
was brought to the base of the mountain. Intensive cardiac care
failed to revive him and he was pronounced dead at 5:50 p.m.
</P>
<P>
Kennedy was the second of the 11 children born to the former
senator and his wife, Ethel, to die under tragic circumstances. His
brother David died in Florida in 1984 of a drug overdose.
</P>
<P>
Once viewed as the next political star in the Kennedy family,
Michael suffered a fall from grace last Spring when he was accused
of having had an affair with his family's baby-sitter.
</P>
<P>
But investigations were abandoned after the woman, now a
college student, and her family refused to press charges.
</P>
<P>
The sudden death of Michael Kennedy marks another blow to the
Kennedy family.
</P>
<P>
When Michael was 5, his uncle, President John F. Kennedy, was
assassinated in Dallas in November 1963. Five years later, his
father Robert F. Kennedy was gunned down in Los Angeles in his
presidential race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
